The paper deals with computing the Fourier transform in sublinear time in the presence of noise, which is a problem in signal processing (cs.SP) and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on sparsity suggests that it may also be relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of continuous signals suggests that it may be relevant to systems and control (cs.SI).
